#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:55
msgid "The monitor menu contains controls for viewing and navigating through the clips in your project for the purpose of making edits and seeing the effects of your changes.  Depending on which monitor window you have selected at the time, the controls will affect either the currently selected clip in the Project Bin (**Clip Monitor**) or the playhead in the Timeline (**Project Monitor**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:58
msgid "With the exception of the :menuselection:`Deinterlacer` and :menuselection:`Interpolation` items, it is much more practical to perform the actions on this menu using the associated keyboard shortcuts or the buttons at the bottom of the monitor windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:64
msgid "**Switch Monitor**: Toggles between clip monitor and project monitor. when the project monitor is in focus the timeline is focus as well. Keyboard Shortcut :kbd:`T`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:68
msgid "**Focus Timecode**: Focus to the timecode on the active monitor so you can change the timecode to the place you want to jump to. Keyboard shortcut :kbd:`=`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:74
msgid "**Play**: Start playing the monitor in focus with shortcut :kbd:`space`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:78
msgid "**Play Zone**: Plays from in-point to the out-point of a zone. Keyboard Shortcut :kbd:`Ctrl + space`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:82
msgid "**Play Zone From Cursor**: Plays from the playhead to the out-point of a zone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:86
msgid "**Loop Zone**: Plays from in-point to the out-point of a zone in a loop. Keyboard Shortcut :kbd:`Ctrl + shift + space`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:90
msgid "**Loop Selected Clip**: This works in the timeline only. Plays from the first to the last selected clip in the timeline in a loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:97
msgid "Go To"
msgstr ""

