#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:120
msgid "Seek Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:128
msgid "**Set Zone In**: This set the point where a zone starts. Shortcut :kbd:`I`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:132
msgid "**Set Zone Out**: This set the point where a zone ends. Shortcut :kbd:`O`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:136
msgid "**Insert Zone in Project Bin**: When you have created a zone you can put the zone with this command into the project bin as a sub-clip of the original clip. This is useful when you have a long clip and you want only some parts of it. Shortcut :kbd:`Ctrl + I`. Another possibility is to use :ref:`markers_with_range`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:145
msgid "**Switch Monitor Fullscreen**: Switch the monitor to full screen when pressing :kbd:`F11` or double-clicking in the monitor. You can set the target monitor via :menuselection:`Menu --> Settings --> Configure Kdenlive --> Playback --> Monitor for fullscreen output`. The mouse cursor is automatically hidden after two seconds (if the mouse hasn't been moved) and automatically be shown again when the user moves the mouse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:147
msgid "If you have more than 1 monitor you can enable :menuselection:`Menu --> Settings --> Configure Kdenlive --> Playback --> Mirror monitor on fullscreen` and a basic real mirror is shown on fullscreen (it doesn't show the final output in case of multi-cam view yet). This keeps the monitor as it is but shows a duplicate full screen playback on another monitor without seekbar at the bottom. This is useful to show another person or audience the same view on a secondary screen, such as a TV, for feedback, or to view footage on a larger, more color-accurate display."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:151
msgid "**Multitrack View**: Multitrack view is described in detail :ref:`here <ui-multitrack_view>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:155
msgid "**Zoom In Monitor**: Zooms in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:159
msgid "**Zoom Out Monitor**: Zooms out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:163
msgid "**Current Monitor Overlay**: Opens a fly-out for the various available monitor overlays. More details see in :ref:`Clip Monitor <ui-monitors_cm_rightclick>` or :ref:`Project Monitor <ui-monitors_pm_right_click>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:167
msgid "**Preview Resolution**: Preview resolution is described in detail :ref:`here <ui-monitors_preview_resolution>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/menu/monitor_menu.rst:171
msgid "**Monitor Config**: Opens a fly-out for the various available monitor configurations. More details see in :ref:`Clip Monitor <ui-monitors_cm_rightclick>` or :ref:`Project Monitor <ui-monitors_pm_right_click>`."
msgstr ""
